# Typography Standards

## Font Stack

Use one distinctive serif for headings paired with system sans for body:

```css
:root {
  /* Primary serif for headings - choose ONE */
  --font-serif: 'Signifier', Georgia, serif;
  /* Alternative options: 'Tiempos', 'GT Sectra', 'Freight Text' */
  
  /* System sans for body text */
  --font-sans: system-ui, -apple-system, BlinkMacSystemFont, 'Segoe UI', sans-serif;
  
  /* Monospace for code */
  --font-mono: ui-monospace, 'SF Mono', SFMono-Regular, Menlo, Consolas, monospace;
}
```

## Type Scale

Constrained, intentional sizes only:

```css
:root {
  --text-xs: 0.75rem;     /* 12px - captions, metadata */
  --text-sm: 0.8125rem;   /* 13px - secondary text, code */
  --text-base: 0.875rem;  /* 14px - body text */
  --text-lg: 1.125rem;    /* 18px - lead paragraphs */
  --text-xl: 1.5rem;      /* 24px - section headings */
  --text-2xl: 2rem;       /* 32px - page titles (rare) */
}
```

## Letter Spacing

Tighten headings, leave body alone:

```css
h1, h2, h3 {
  letter-spacing: -0.025em;
}

.heading-tight {
  letter-spacing: -0.01em;
}

/* Body text: default tracking (0) */
```

## Line Height

```css
:root {
  --leading-tight: 1.2;   /* headings */
  --leading-normal: 1.5;  /* UI elements */
  --leading-relaxed: 1.6; /* body text, paragraphs */
}

body {
  line-height: var(--leading-relaxed);
}

h1, h2, h3 {
  line-height: var(--leading-tight);
}
```

## Font Weights

Stay in the 400-500 range. Bold is rarely needed:

```css
/* ❌ Avoid */
font-weight: 700;
font-weight: bold;

/* ✅ Prefer */
font-weight: 400; /* normal */
font-weight: 500; /* medium - for emphasis */
font-weight: 600; /* semibold - rare, headings only */
```

## Font Loading

Always use font-display swap and preload critical fonts:

```css
@font-face {
  font-family: 'Signifier';
  src: url('/fonts/signifier-regular.woff2') format('woff2');
  font-weight: 400;
  font-style: normal;
  font-display: swap;
}
```

```html
<!-- In <head> -->
<link rel="preload" href="/fonts/signifier-regular.woff2" as="font" type="font/woff2" crossorigin>
```

## Anti-Aliasing

Always enable for crisp text:

```css
body {
  -webkit-font-smoothing: antialiased;
  -moz-osx-font-smoothing: grayscale;
}
```
